description.p:
In a first aspect, the invention provides a method of producing an acellular nerve graft comprising the steps of:
providing a section of nerve;
optional primary treatment of the section of nerve comprising freezing and then thawing the section of peripheral nerve;
freeze-drying the (optionally freeze-thawed) section of nerve longitudinally to introduce longitudinal pores into the section of nerve; and
decellularization of the section of nerve comprising contacting the freeze-dried section of nerve with detergent and enzymatic decellularization agents to provide the acellular nerve graft.

In one embodiment, the invention provides an acellular peripheral nerve graft characterised by comprising:
a length of at least 50 mm;
longitudinal pores having an average pore size of at least 40 m;
a DNA content of less than 100 ng/mg;
a native nerve structure with retention of nerve fascicles and connective tissue layers, endoneurium, perineuriem and epineurium; and
optionally, a sulphated glycosaminoglycan (sGAG) content of greater than 0.21 μg/mg.
